data.title: Pospisil falls in semfinal
data.meta_description: Vernon’s Vasek Pospisil and partner Daniel Nestor of Toronto fell in the semifinals of men’s doubles at the Roger’s Cup
data.text:
Vernon’s Vasek Pospisil and partner Daniel Nestor of Toronto fell in the semifinals of men’s doubles at the Roger’s Cup tennis championships in Toronto.

Pospisil and Nestor, ranked sixth, lost 6-4, 6-7, 10-7 to second-ranked Jamie Murray of England and Bruno Soares of Brazil.

Pospisil and Nestor will represent Canada in men’s doubles at the Rio Olympics.
